data.chText: 出产（作物）；产生（收益、效益等）；提供
data.enText: to produce or provide sth, for example a profit, result or crop

data.chText: 高利率的存款会产生丰厚的收益。
data.enText: Higher-rate deposit accounts yield good returns.

data.chText: 这项研究提供了有用的资料。
data.enText: The research has yielded useful information.

data.chText: 不再结果实的树
data.enText: trees that no longer yield fruit

data.chText: 屈服；让步
data.enText: to stop resisting sth/sb; to agree to do sth that you do not want to do

data.chText: 经过长时间的包围，这座孤城被迫投降。
data.enText: After a long siege, the town was forced to yield.

data.chText: 他不情愿地屈从于他们的要求。
data.enText: He reluctantly yielded to their demands.

data.chText: 我经不住诱惑，吃了一大块巧克力。
data.enText: I yielded to temptation and had a chocolate bar.

data.chText: 放弃；缴出
data.enText: to allow sb to win, have or take control of sth that has been yours until now

data.chText: 他拒绝缴枪。
data.enText: He refused to yield up his gun.

data.chText: 宇宙慢慢地展现出它的秘密。
data.enText: The universe is slowly yielding up its secrets.

data.chText: （受压）活动，变形，弯曲，折断
data.enText: to move, bend or break because of pressure

data.chText: 这把锁我们砸也砸不开。
data.enText: Despite our attempts to break it, the lock would not yield.

data.chText: 给（大路上的车辆）让路
data.enText: to allow vehicles on a bigger road to go first

data.chText: 给迎面驶来的车辆让路。
data.enText: Yield to oncoming traffic.

data.chText: 让车标志
data.enText: a yield sign
yield to sth

data.chText: 被…替代；为…所取代
data.enText: to be replaced by sth

data.chText: 在货物运输方面，驳船让位给了公路车辆。
data.enText: Barges yielded to road vehicles for transporting goods.

data.chText: 产量；产出；利润
data.enText: the total amount of crops, profits, etc. that are produced

data.chText: 作物丰收
data.enText: a high crop yield

data.chText: 牛奶产量的降低
data.enText: a reduction in milk yield

data.chText: 这会给你的投资带来10%的利润。
data.enText: This will give a yield of 10% on your investment.

ex.enText: The soldiers vowed that they would rather die than surrender.

ex.chText: 我们决不会向邪恶势力低头。
ex.enText: We will never surrender to evil.

ex.chText: 在这种压力下，你能不屈服吗?
ex.enText: Couldn't you surrender under such pressure?

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指因战败而投降，或指在压力下屈服让步，常后接介词 to。

ex.enText: The rebels were forced to give in.

ex.chText: 他最后向妻子作出了让步。
ex.enText: Finally, he gave in to his wife.

ex.chText: 只有懦夫才向命运屈服。
ex.enText: Only a coward gives in to his fate.

synonyms.bx: 用法不如 surrender 正式，可后接介词 to。

ex.enText: They did not submit to the enemy.

ex.chText: 矿工们面对威胁，拒不低头。
ex.enText: The miners refused to submit to threats.

ex.chText: 你怎么能甘受这种虐待呢?
ex.enText: How could you submit to such ill treatment?

synonyms.bx: 通常指放弃抵抗，屈服于某一势力、权力、意志等。

ex.chText: 我们决不会向侵略者屈服。
ex.enText: We will never yield to invaders.
He didn't yield himself to his rival.

ex.chText: 我尊重法律，不会屈服于任何压力。
ex.enText: I won't yield to any pressure in my respect for the law.

synonyms.bx: 通常指放弃抵抗而投降，也可指因缺乏坚强的意志、忍耐力等而屈从于某种权势或压力，常后接介词 to。

ex.zh: 拒绝屈服（或交出、让路）；无论如何都不移位

data.enText: yield to sth

data.chText: 被…替代；为…所取代
data.enText: to be replaced by sth

data.chText: 在货物运输方面，驳船让位给了公路车辆。
data.enText: Barges yielded to road vehicles for transporting goods.

tr: the income or profit arising from such transactions as the sale of land or other property
the quantity of something (as a commodity) that is created (usually within a given period of time)
example: production was up in the second quarter

tr: end resistance, as under pressure or force
example: The door yielded to repeated blows with a battering ram

tr: be flexible under stress of physical force

example: The cow brings in 5 liters of milk
This year's crop yielded 1,000 bushels of corn
The estate renders some revenue for the family

tr: cause to happen or be responsible for
example: His two singles gave the team the victory

tr: move in order to make room for someone for something
example: The park gave way to a supermarket
How much does this savings certificate pay annually?

tr: surrender or relinquish to the physical control of another
be the cause or source of
example: He gave me a lot of trouble
Our meeting afforded much interesting information

tr: give in, as to influence or pressure

value.def: If you yield to someone or something, you stop resisting them.

example.ex: Will she yield to growing pressure for her to retire?...
example.tran: 面对要求其隐退的压力越来越大，她会屈服吗？

example.ex: I yielded to an impulse...
example.tran: 我没有忍住冲动。

example.ex: If the government does not yield, it should face sufficient military force to ensure its certain and swift defeat.
example.tran: 如果政府不让步，它就会面临重兵围困，必将迅速落败。

value.def: If you yield something that you have control of or responsibility for, you allow someone else to have control or responsibility for it

example.ex: He may yield control...
example.tran: 他可能会放弃控制权。

example.ex: The President is now under pressure to yield power to the republics.
example.tran: 总统现在面临着让权给共和党人的压力。

example.ex: Giulio Andreotti yielded up the prime ministership last summer.
example.tran: 朱利奥·安德烈奥蒂去年夏天辞去了总理之职。

value.def: If one thing yields to another thing, it is replaced by this other thing.

example.ex: Boston's traditional drab brick was slow to yield to the modern glass palaces of so many American urban areas.
example.tran: 波士顿传统而单调的砖石建筑并没有迅速被许多美国城市地区流行的现代玻璃大厦所取代。

value.def: If a moving person or a vehicle yields, they slow down or stop in order to allow other people or vehicles to pass in front of them.

example.ex: When entering a trail or starting a descent, yield to other skiers.
example.tran: 进入滑雪道或开始下滑时，要给其他滑雪者让路。

example.ex: ...examples of common signs like No Smoking or Yield.
example.tran: “请勿吸烟”或“让行”之类的常见标志的例子

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 give way

value.def: If something yields, it breaks or moves position because force or pressure has been put on it.

example.ex: The door yielded easily when he pushed it.
example.tran: 他一推，门就开了。

value.def: If an area of land yields a particular amount of a crop, this is the amount that is produced. You can also say that a number of animals yield a particular amount of meat.

example.ex: Last year 400,000 acres of land yielded a crop worth $1.75 billion.
example.tran: 去年40万英亩的土地产值达17.5亿美元。

example.ex: The shallow sea bed yields up an abundance of food.
example.tran: 浅海床提供了丰富的食物。

value.def: A yield is the amount of food produced on an area of land or by a number of animals.

example.ex: ...improving the yield of the crop...
example.tran: 提高农作物产量

example.ex: Polluted water lessens crop yields.
example.tran: 受污染的水源会降低农作物产量。

value.def: If a tax or investment yields an amount of money or profit, this money or profit is obtained from it.

example.ex: It yielded a profit of at least $36 million.
example.tran: 它带来了至少3,600万美元的收益。

value.tran: （税收或投资）产生，带来（收益或效益）

value.def: A yield is the amount of money or profit produced by an investment.

example.ex: ...a yield of 4%...
example.tran: 4%的收益

example.ex: The high yields available on the dividend shares made them attractive to private investors.
example.tran: 红利股票的高收益率对私人投资者极具吸引力。

example.ex: ...the yield on a bank's investments.
example.tran: 一家银行投资带来的收益

gramarinfo.label: with supp, oft N <l>of</l> amount, N <l>on</l> n

value.def: If something yields a result or piece of information, it produces it.

example.ex: This research has been in progress since 1961 and has yielded a great number of positive results...
example.tran: 这项研究自1961年起一直在开展，已取得了不少积极成果。

example.ex: His trip to Melbourne had yielded a lot of information.
example.tran: 他的墨尔本之行让他大开眼界。
